cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Kazakh Language Understanding Benchmark"
message: "If you use this dataset or code, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: "Timur"
    family-names: "Seidalin"
    alias: "Tim2190"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Tim2190/kazakh-factcheck-benchmark"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.21382433"
abstract: >-
  A pilot benchmark probing how well large language models understand the
  Kazakh language along two complementary tracks. Track A (fact-checking):
  60 hand-built claims over three genres (legal, news, informal code-mixed
  dialogue), each faithful or deliberately distorted by a fixed taxonomy
  (number, entity, causal-relation, invented), verified open-book with a
  grounding gate. Track B (idioms): 30 native-verified Kazakh idioms with a
  two-phase comprehension task (with and without a usage example),
  human-adjudicated. Five LLMs from five labs are evaluated.
keywords:
  - Kazakh
  - low-resource NLP
  - language understanding
  - fact-checking
  - idioms
  - phraseology
  - hallucination
  - large language models
  - benchmark
license: CC-BY-4.0
version: "1.0.0-pilot"
date-released: "2026-07-14"
